modules.description: Provides solvers for initial value problems of ordinary differential equations using explicit and implicit methods. Accepts user-defined functions for the derivative and handles arrays of real numbers representing state variables. Used to model dynamic systems such as population growth, chemical reactions, and mechanical motion.

Provides solvers for initial value problems of ordinary differential equations, including root-finding capabilities. Operates on vectors and matrices represented as Bigarray arrays, with functions to advance solutions, track roots, and retrieve solution values. Used for simulating dynamic systems where numerical integration and event detection are required.
